<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<h2 id="extension-to-article-50">Extension to Article 50</h2>
<p>Article 50 has been extended until 31 January 2020, with the option to leave earlier as soon as a deal has been ratified.  The Government’s preference is to leave with a deal. However, if the Withdrawal Agreement is not ratified by UK and EU Parliaments then the default position of no deal remains.</p>

<h2 id="implementation-period-in-a-deal-scenario">Implementation period in a ‘deal’ scenario</h2>

<p>Should a deal be ratified the date on which the UK will leave the EU will be announced. From this date we will enter into an ‘implementation period’ until 31 December 2020.  There is no implementation period if the UK leaves the EU in a no-deal scenario.</p>

<p>We are continuing to prepare for all scenarios which include making improvements to current Brexit planning and future services.</p>

<p>UK businesses will continue to have the same rights during the implementation period as EU-based businesses to have their cases and applications accepted and processed by EU-based ‘leading authorities’.</p>

<p>During the implementation period the government will continue to negotiate with the EU and agree on the details which will form the Brexit deal.  It will also be the time during which businesses and the government can prepare and adjust to these new arrangements, as they unfold.</p>

<p>Information on what you need to do during the implementation period and how to prepare for the Brexit deal will be made available here, in due course.</p>

<div class="call-to-action">
<p>Sign up to our <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/email-signup/new?email_signup%5Bfeed%5D=https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/veterinary-medicines-directorate.atom">email alert</a> notifications to make sure you get the latest information as it becomes available.</p>
</div>

<h2 id="brexit-information-hubhttpwwwvmddefragovukonlinewheeleuexitinformationhubpdf-in-a-no-deal-scenario">
<a rel="external" href="http://www.vmd.defra.gov.uk/online/wheel/EUExitInformationHub.pdf">Brexit Information Hub</a> in a ‘no deal’ scenario</h2>

<p>Click on each section of this Hub, which shows what areas of the regulation of veterinary medicines will and will not change. It also provides draft guidance that will be current on EU Exit day. Use this information to understand how leaving the EU may affect your business and what you can do to get ready.</p>

<figure class="image embedded"><div class="img"><img src="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/image_data/file/84816/EUExit_wheel.jpg" alt="EUExit Wheel"></img></div></figure>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/vmd-eu-exit-information-hub-accessible-format">Accessible format version of the Information Hub</a> If you use assistive technology (such as a screen reader) and need a version of this document in a more accessible format, please email <a href="mailto:postmaster@vmd.gov.uk">postmaster@vmd.gov.uk</a> telling us what format you need. It will help us if you say what assistive technology you use.</p>

